tty weird since many will claim without even asking how they prove such things happen in real life):\n\u2013First, let us imagine this sea level rise was caused by melting ice sheets on Antarctica or Greenland\u2013and while most think both locations don\u2019t contribute that much to overall global warming because their size isn\u2019t nearly as important compared with other factors like carbon dioxide emissions (which we know come from humans and hence do not have anything natural about them), there\u2019s still room for doubt given how difficult they can sometimes appear in computer simulations which try modeling these complicated systems\u2013so what should happen if this theory was correct instead of global warming being behind it?\nShouldn\u2019t the water actually rise more evenly across the ocean surface without any specific zones noticeably increasing faster than others? The answer is yes, since",
